  "body": "I would like to modify the WETH balance of my contract prior to execute some simulation via `eth_call`.  I would like to apply override to the storage state of WETH contract\r\n\r\nI have tested my storage slot & value calculation in foundry and they are correct.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction getStorageLocationForKey(address _key, uint index) public pure returns(bytes32) {\r\n        return keccak256(abi.encode(_key, index));\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction testWETHBalanceOverwrite() public {\r\n        uint index = 3;\r\n        address contractAddress = 0x22B055fd76a699a47176731D7A2516DBc3956f1C;\r\n        console.log(\"before overwrite\");\r\n        emit log_named_uint(\"WETH balance before\", IERC20(WETH).balanceOf(contractAddress));\r\n        vm.store(WETH, getStorageLocationForKey(contractAddress, index), bytes32(uint(2000 ether)));\r\n        emit log_named_uint(\"WETH balance after\", IERC20(WETH).balanceOf(contractAddress));\r\n        emit log_named_bytes32(\"storage\", getStorageLocationForKey(contractAddress, index));\r\n        emit log_named_bytes32(\"value\", bytes32(uint(2000 ether)));\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n``` \r\n\r\n```\r\nLogs:\r\n  before overwrite\r\n  WETH balance before: 711955326957954493\r\n  WETH balance after: 2000000000000000000000\r\n  storage: 0x1a0fc6602d9ab6683b5e7c92ab33a9dd3192422f187802d978da9bd52fd91dd4\r\n  value: 0x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000006c6b935b8bbd400000\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, when I copy the storageHash and valueHash for use in go-ethereum, it doesn't work. \r\n\r\n```\r\nstorageHash := common.HexToHash(\"0x1a0fc6602d9ab6683b5e7c92ab33a9dd3192422f187802d978da9bd52fd91dd4\")\r\nvalueHash := common.HexToHash(\"0x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000006c6b935b8bbd400000\")\r\n\r\noverrides[WETH] = gethclient.OverrideAccount{\r\nStateDiff: map[common.Hash]common.Hash{\r\n\tstorageHash: valueHash,\r\n},\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I remove the override, call to WETH.balanceOf(contractAddress) returns the correct balance. With this override above, it returns empty data.\r\n\r\n\r\nQuestion:\r\n\r\nWhat am I doing wrong ? How do I properly apply the override ? ",
